header.gameNote: OREGON RAIN INVITATIONAL AT CORVALLIS OR

article.headline: Southeastern Louisiana 76, Cal Poly 69
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Senior Quennell Green scored 21 points and had six rebounds to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 76-69 victory over Cal Poly in the Oregon Rain Invitational Friday night. Daryl Cohen added 17 points and Kevyn Green and Terry Bryant each added 15 for the Lions in their season opener. Green, a Portland, Ore., native, is the nephew of former Oregon State star A.C. Green. Southeastern, which finished 16-12 last season, plays the Beavers on Saturday in the round-robin tournament at Gill Coliseum. Derek Stockalper had 15 points and Dawin Whiten added 14 for the Mustangs, who led 41-28 at the half. Stockalper led Cal Poly last season, averaging 12.9 points and 6.7 rebounds. The Mustangs, who finished 10-19 last season, will play Portland on Saturday. The Oregon Rain Invitational is the first in-season tournament hosted by Oregon State since the 1959-60 season.
